&lt;p&gt;We are very excited to be advertising for a transition specialist nurse for the young people with long term conditions who receive their care and treatment at Frimley Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following a review of our paediatric nursing structure we can offer a full time position, covering both acute sites of Frimley Park and Wexham Park&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be highly motivated, professional, caring, able to advocate on behalf of young people, be empathetic with a passion for encouraging self care as the young people move into adult care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide a bespoke local induction/orientation programme for you and support your development to meet your full potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a number of multi- disciplinary teams including but not limited to diabetes, epilepsy, respiratory, oncology with dynamic lead clinicians and specialist nurses who will support you in your role to move young people forwards into their next stage of managing their long term condition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ros Rushworth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Head of nursing&lt;/p&gt;
